entry.title: Three-Way Train Crash in India Kills More Than 250: 'I Haven't Seen Anything So Horrific'
entry.content: A three-way train crash in India killed at least 261 people and injured hundreds more, in one of the deadliest rail accidents in the country’s history.

entry.title: A Month of Russian Missile Attacks Leaves Kyiv Residents on Edge
entry.content: Ukraine’s capital has endured the most sustained barrage since the start of the invasion. Some are struggling to cope.

entry.title: Russia, Ukraine Trade Artillery Fire at Border
entry.content: In Ukraine’s Kharkiv and Sumy regions, Russian shelling killed at least one civilian, while inside Russia, five civilians were killed by rocket fire in the Belgorod region.
